LEGISLATURE OF NEBRASKA
ONE HUNDRED NINTH LEGISLATURE
SECOND SESSION
LEGISLATIVE BILL 954
Introduced by von Gillern, 4.
Read first time January 12, 2026
Committee: Revenue
1 A BILL FOR AN ACT relating to the Nebraska Advantage Act; to amend
2 section 77-5701, Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska; to provide
3 for the recalculation of base-year employees as prescribed; to
4 harmonize provisions; and to repeal the original section.
5 Be it enacted by the people of the State of Nebraska,
-1-

LB954 LB954
2026 2026
1 Section 1. Section 77-5701, Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska, is
2 amended to read:
3 77-5701 Sections 77-5701 to 77-5735 and section 2 of this act shall
4 be known and may be cited as the Nebraska Advantage Act.
5 Sec. 2. (1) If a taxpayer who has met the required levels of
6 employment and investment contained in an agreement for a tier 6 project
7 sells a portion of the business operations that were subject to such
8 agreement and the business operations that were sold continue to operate
9 under an entity that is not part of the same unitary group as the
10 taxpayer, the Department of Revenue shall recalculate the taxpayer's
11 base-year employees by subtracting the number of equivalent employees
12 employed at the business operations that were sold from the number of
13 base-year employees calculated for the taxpayer on the last Form 312N
14 filed prior to the date of sale.
15 (2) This section shall not apply:
16 (a) If the business operations that were sold as described in
17 subsection (1) of this section cease all operations within twenty-four
18 months after the date of sale; or
19 (b) If the primary business purpose of the sale described in
20 subsection (1) of this section was to close a location.
21 (3) Any credits or other incentives generated prior to a sale
22 described in subsection (1) of this section shall not be recalculated.
23 (4) This section applies to agreements entered into after December
24 31, 2016.
25 Sec. 3. Original section 77-5701, Reissue Revised Statutes of
26 Nebraska, is repealed.
